Geert Uytterhoeven wrote:
> There are: some Amiga video boards use little endian PCI video chips connected
> through a hardware byteswapping Zorro<->PCI FPGA.
Another fun device is the Efficient Networks ENI155 ATM NIC series: they
have an SBus chip behind a PCI-SBus bridge. Of course, probably 99% of
the NICs they've produced are PCI ... (which, fortunately, makes it
quite unlikely that we'll ever need to support the SBus original)
- Werner
